value.0: Ooh you poor dear!... I saw the boat crash. Are you alright?
I am sure it wont be broke long. After all nothing seems like it will effect you long at all.
Ahhh Well it will heal quickly enough for one of your breeding.
That is terrible. Not everyone escapes without a wound. I suggest ending into the Healers in town. It is in the western side.  I am sure they will get you all fixed up.
Well... *has a light cheerful tone* Welcome to the land we know as Omen. What it was called before... Well no one seems to know. I do hope you were not expecting to see a Sun Rise any time soon.
We really do not know. But we do know if you go far enough away from here you can see the sun again.
*peers at you almost as if he can see through you*
For you I would reconmend to town. There is a lake on the southern edge. There you should find someone who may speak with you about what to do next.
WHY OF COURSE!!! I can tell you lots of things. Things on the city,  things to do, places to aviod and much more. What do you seek to know about? *seems overly cheery in such a dark place*
There is the man known only as Cookie, he collects rat parts.
There is a tower just out the south gate that has men in it which have been mugging people.
There is also this place said to be in the tunnels under the city which has strange men and rats. Prehaps that would work as well.
Well that is a little tricky to say. I Can tell you places that could be dangerous.
When you are new to the island I suggest avoiding the big house in the center of the graveyard. As well as any of the buildings west of it. They have many dangerous things with in.
Only that if you can enter a place and it does not have a sign I would be careful. Many places have been known to cause harm if they are not marked by the people.
Well you are in Omen now... At least that is what we were told it was called.
Not Really there is not anyone that we have found that has been here since the city was founded. There is not even a sign of when it was founded.
Yes there is. There is an order of six people. They have been here the longest as far as we can tell.
Noooo Cluuuue! But I hear she is pretty!
What was that you want to know more!!!??
For you I would reconmend going into town to the Haven Tavern. It has food and drink. You may even be able to find some work in town.
For you I would reconmend going into town to the Haven Tavern and Inn. There is a door in the back corner you will find interesting enough.
